	"Description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2 - Kernel-5.15 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2024-42154:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ntcp_metrics: validate source addr length\n\nCVE-2024-41091:\n\tkernel: virtio-net: tun: mlx5_core short frame denial of service\n\nCVE-2024-41090:\n\tkernel: virtio-net: tap: mlx5_core short frame denial of service\n\nCVE-2024-41055:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmm: prevent derefencing NULL ptr in pfn_section_valid()\n\nCVE-2024-41049:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfilelock: fix potential use-after-free in posix_lock_inode\n\nCVE-2024-41041:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nudp: Set SOCK_RCU_FREE earlier in udp_lib_get_port().\n\nCVE-2024-41035:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nUSB: core: Fix duplicate endpoint bug by clearing reserved bits in the descriptor\n\nCVE-2024-41020:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfilelock: Fix fcntl/close race recovery compat path\n\nCVE-2024-41019:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs/ntfs3: Validate ff offset\n\nCVE-2024-41009:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf: Fix overrunning reservations in ringbuf\n\nCVE-2024-36484:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: relax socket state check at accept time.\n\nCVE-2022-48666:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nscsi: core: Fix a use-after-free\n",
